sections.markdown: # Show me all requests with HTTP 5xx but without the 503s. And please ignore all the noisy /health requests that we know that they fail from time to time...

input.value:
fetch spans
| filter NOT(contains(http.target, "health"))
| filter isNotNull(http.status_code)
| fieldsAdd toLong(http.status_code), alias: http.status_code
| filter http.status_code >= 500 AND http.status_code != 503
| summarize count(), alias: cnt, by: {http.target, http.status_code}
| filter cnt > 20
| fieldsAdd targetandcode = concat(http.target, " - ", http.status_code)
| fieldsKeep targetandcode, cnt
| sort cnt desc

sections.markdown: # How much exceptions did we see within the last 2h where the exception message contains "timeout"

input.value:
fetch spans, from: now() -2h, to: now(), scanLimitGBytes: 500, samplingRatio: 1
| filter isNotNull(span.events_as_json)
| parse span.events_as_json, "JSON_ARRAY:exceptions"
| filter arraySize(exceptions) == 1
| fieldsAdd exception = exceptions[0]
| filter exception[span_event.name] != ""
| filter exception[exception.type] != ""
| filter contains(exception[exception.message], "timeout")
| summarize count(), by:{bin(start_time, 1m)}

  | filter db.name != ""
  | filter dt.entity.service.name == "JourneyService"
  | filter startsWith(db.statement, "select")
  | filter db.statement != ""
  | sort cnt desc], sourceField: trace.id, lookupField: trace.id, prefix: "look."
| filter isNotNull(look.trace.id)
| summarize count(), alias: cnt, by: {http.target, look.db.statement}
| filter  cnt > 10 AND cnt < 10000
| sort cnt desc
